initial_story:
The Eurovision Song Contest is just around the corner and this year, it's taking place in Malmo, Sweden.

You can find out all about the event right here.

The UK's entry for 2024 is Olly Alexander who'll be performing his song, Dizzy.

But how's he feeling ahead of the big night, where he'll perform in front of 200 million people!

De-Graft sat down with him to find out all about his preparation for the competition.

The Eurovision Song contest Grand Final will be shown on BBC One and iPlayer on Saturday 11 May.
stories: Olly Alexander: "I'm feeling really excited and a bit nervous, to be honest. It's a huge platform and I'm just trying to soak it all in. We've been rehearsing for weeks now and I think we're in a good place. The song is really special to me and I'm hoping the audience will connect with it. I've been listening to a lot of past Eurovision winners to get inspiration and I'm feeling quite confident. But, you know, it's a competition and anything can happen!"

"I'm just trying to focus on the performance and not think too much about the outcome. I know the other contestants are all talented in their own ways, so I'm just hoping our unique energy and message will shine through. The backing vocalists have been amazing to work with, and our choreographer has come up with some really cool moves. I'm just hoping the audience will get lost in the music and forget about everything else. Bring it on, Eurovision!"

"I can already feel the adrenaline pumping as we get ready to take the stage. I'm trying to stay calm and focused, but it's hard not to get caught up in the excitement of it all. I've been visualizing our performance in my head a million times, and I just know we're going to crush it. The crowd is going to love us, and I can already imagine the energy in the room. Let's do this!"

"As I take a deep breath and step out into the bright lights, I can feel the roar of the crowd growing louder and the anticipation building. I glance over at my bandmates, and we share a nod of solidarity before launching into the first song. The music starts, and I'm completely in the zone, lost in the rhythm and the moment. The crowd is singing along, and I can feel the energy coursing through me like a powerful force. This is what it's all about – the rush of performing live, the thrill of connecting with the audience, and the sense of accomplishment when it's all over and we've given it our all."

"As the night wears on, the energy only builds, and I find myself feeding off the crowd's enthusiasm, my voice soaring on the choruses and my guitar work becoming more frenetic and intense. The sweat is dripping down my face, and my fingers are numb from the constant strumming, but I'm in a zone, completely absorbed in the music and the moment. We launch into our hit single, and the crowd erupts, singing along with every word, and I feel like I'm on top of the world, like nothing can stop us from taking over the stage and owning the night."

"The rush of adrenaline is intoxicating, and I lose myself in the performance, the music becoming a blur of sound and fury as I pour every ounce of energy into the show. The crowd is a sea of faces, all united in their passion and devotion, and I feel like I'm connected to each and every one of them, our collective energy building to a crescendo that threatens to consume us all. And then, in the midst of the chaos, I see her - the girl in the front row, her eyes locked on mine, a look of pure adoration on her face, and I know in that moment that this is what it's all about, this is what makes all the hard work and sacrifice worth it."

"As I lock eyes with her, I feel a jolt of electricity run through my veins, and I'm suddenly aware of the entire room fading away, leaving only the two of us, suspended in a moment of pure connection. The music swirls around us, a sonic backdrop to the intense emotion building between us, and I can feel my heart pounding in my chest like a drum. I'm not sure how much longer I can keep my gaze fixed on hers, but I'm powerless to look away, mesmerized by the depth of feeling in her eyes. The crowd is still there, still cheering and screaming, but it's all just background noise, a distant hum, as I'm drawn deeper into the vortex of her adoration."

"The air is charged with tension as we stand there, the only sound the heavy breathing between us. I can feel her eyes burning into mine, like a brand searing itself into my skin, and I'm acutely aware of every inch of her face, every curve and contour, every delicate feature that makes her so uniquely beautiful. The music reaches a crescendo, the beat pounding in time with my racing heart, and I'm convinced that if I don't touch her soon, I'll explode into a thousand pieces. My hand reaches out, as if of its own accord, and brushes against hers, sending a jolt of electricity through both of us. The crowd erupts into cheers once more, but I barely register it, my focus fixed on the woman who's captured me, body and soul."

"As our eyes lock, the music fades into the background, and the only sound is the pounding of my heart in my ears. I can feel the electricity coursing through my veins, like a live wire humming with energy. Her hand, warm and soft, is still pressed against mine, and I'm desperate to explore every inch of her skin, to see if the sparks that flew between us are just a one-time fluke or if they're a sign of something more. The crowd, the music, the world around us melts away, leaving only the two of us, suspended in this moment of pure, unadulterated desire. I take a step closer, my heart racing with anticipation, and she doesn't back away, her eyes never leaving mine. The air is thick with tension, heavy with the promise of something new, something forbidden, something that could change everything."

"I can see the flicker of desire in her eyes, a spark that mirrors the one burning within me. Her pupils are dilated, her breathing shallow, and I can sense the same primal urge coursing through her veins. The distance between us shrinks, and I can feel the heat emanating from her skin, drawing me in like a magnet. My hand tightens around hers, the pressure a gentle warning, a promise of what's to come. I lean in, my mouth inches from hers, and she doesn't flinch, her gaze locked on mine like a challenge, a dare to take the next step, to surrender to the passion building between us."

"As I hover, poised on the brink of claiming her lips, I'm met with a flash of defiance in her eyes, a spark of resistance that only heightens my desire. "The taste of her lips is like a shot of pure adrenaline, coursing through my veins and leaving me breathless. I deepen the kiss, my tongue tangling with hers in a dance of desire. "As our lips break apart, I gaze into her eyes, searching for any sign of hesitation or doubt, but all I find is a burning intensity that matches my own. "And then, without warning, her hand reaches up to cup my cheek, her fingers tracing the contours of my face with a gentle, exploratory touch. "As I gaze into those piercing depths, I'm transported back to the night we first met, the night that changed everything. "I take a step closer, my heart pounding in my chest, and her eyes never leave mine. The air is charged with an electric tension, and I can feel the weight of our history between us. "As the word hangs in the air, her eyes flash with a mix of surprise and longing, and I can see the faintest tremble in her lips. "The air is charged with electricity as she utters the single syllable, her voice a gentle breeze that rustles the leaves of my soul. "But even as the thought crosses my mind, I sense a flicker of uncertainty in her eyes, a hesitation that makes my heart skip a beat. "So I reach out, my hand brushing against hers, and I look into her eyes, searching for any sign of the connection we once shared. "But as I hold her gaze, I'm met with a mixture of emotions - a hint of sadness, a dash of longing, and a healthy dose of wariness. "Her gaze falters, and for a moment, I think I see a glimmer of the Emily I once knew, the one who laughed with me, who loved me with all her heart. But then, her mask slips back into place, and she looks away, her voice barely above a whisper as she says, 'It's too late, Ryan. You had your chance, and you blew it. I've moved on, and I'm not going back.'"

"I feel like I've been punched in the gut, the air knocked out of me. I try to speak, to tell her that I'm still here, that I still love her, but the words get stuck in my throat. I take a step closer, my eyes locked on hers, and I can see the pain and the anger there, but I also see a hint of sadness, a glimmer of the love we once shared. I reach out, my hand hesitating in mid-air, and then I drop it, feeling like I'm grasping at straws. 'What about us, Emily?' I ask, my voice barely above a whisper, hoping against hope that she'll hear the sincerity in my words, that she'll see the love that's still there, burning bright and true."

"Emily's eyes flash with anger, and for a moment, I think she's going to lash out at me, tell me to leave her alone. But then, something in her expression softens, and she looks away, her gaze drifting to the floor. 'What about us, Ryan?' she repeats, her voice low and husky, and I can hear the pain and the tears behind it. 'What about us, when you were off chasing your dreams, leaving me behind to pick up the pieces of our shattered life? What about us, when you couldn't even be bothered to call me, to check in and see how I was doing?' She takes a step back, her eyes welling up with tears, and I feel like I've been punched again, this time in the chest."

"I take a step forward, my heart racing with guilt and regret, and reach out to her, but she jerks away, her eyes flashing with a mix of anger and hurt. 'Don't touch me,' she whispers, her voice trembling. 'You don't get to touch me after what you did. You don't get to pretend like everything is okay, like you didn't just break my heart into a million pieces.' She takes another step back, her back against the wall, and I can see the tears streaming down her face, her chest heaving with sobs. I feel like I'm drowning in my own regret, unable to do anything but stand there, frozen in shame and remorse."

"I try to speak, to apologize, to make things right, but the words catch in my throat like a lump of lead. I'm not sure what to say, or how to make her understand that I didn't mean for things to go so far. That I didn't mean to hurt her. That I still love her, and I always will. But the words won't come, and I'm left standing there, feeling like the biggest coward in the world. I take a step back, my eyes fixed on hers, and I can see the pain and betrayal written all over her face. I know I have to do something, anything, to make her forgive me, but I'm not sure what that is. All I know is that I have to try."

"I take a deep breath, trying to calm my racing heart, and reach out to her. My hand hovers in mid-air, unsure of what to do with it. I want to hold her, to comfort her, to tell her that everything will be okay. But I'm afraid of being rejected, of being pushed away. I look into her eyes, searching for some glimmer of hope, some sign that she's willing to listen to me. And then, I see it - a flicker of sadness, of longing. It's a small spark, but it's enough to give me the courage to take another step forward. I reach out again, my hand trembling, and gently touch her arm. 'Please,' I whisper, my voice barely audible. 'Please, just listen to me. Let me explain. Let me make it right.'"

"As I speak, I can feel her gaze on me, her eyes burning with a mix of emotions. She looks at me like she's searching for something, like she's trying to read my soul. I hold my breath, waiting for her response, my heart pounding in my chest. And then, to my surprise, she nods. Just a small, almost imperceptible nod, but it's enough to give me hope. 'Okay,' she whispers, her voice barely above a whisper. 'I'll listen. But you have to promise me one thing.' She pauses, her eyes locked on mine, and I can feel my heart racing with anticipation. "'The truth?' I repeat, my voice shaking slightly as I try to process what she's asking. 'What do you mean?' I ask, trying to keep my tone neutral, but my mind racing with the implications. I nod, feeling a sense of determination wash over me. 'I promise,' I say, my voice firm. 'I'll tell you the truth, no matter what.'"

I look down, unable to meet her gaze, my shame and guilt washing over me like a wave."

I'm not sure what the future holds for me, but I do know that I'm excited to see what's next. I hope you can find it in your heart to forgive me for my mistakes, and to know that I'll always cherish the love we shared.
